the second respondent submitted that mr williams' opinion was honestly held, and that he had a proper foundation for the opinion, namely the regard he had to comparable developments at caribbean gardens and a development called the "pellicano development".
the relevant "standard" in terms of a proper foundation for the opinion was that of a real estate agent, rather than that of an independent valuer.
rather, the second respondent "cast its defence in a particular way on the basis of one case and is now faced with a different case that it may have fought differently".